war ii and marrying beverly thrall daughter of the head of the firm by the s the company was making as many as  railcars a year but annual production dropped to about  cars during the s when annual sales were around  million meanwhile duchossois who created a parent company named after himself that expanded into electronic consumer products national defense supplies and various capital goods moved into the horse racing business by purchasing facilities in suburban arlington heights by the mids when railcar production reached  per year annual revenues from horse racing approached  million in  thrall was purchased by trinity industries of dallas texas a leading railcar manufacturer at the beginning of the twentyfirst century the privately held company led by craig duchossois richards son still employed about  people in the chicago area and grossed about  billion in annual sales this entry is part of the encyclopedias dictionary of leading chicago businesses  that was prepared by mark r wilson with additional contributions from stephen r porter and janice l reiff the electronic encyclopedia of chicago   chicago historical society the encyclopedia of chicago   the newberry library all rights reserved portions are copyrighted by other institutions and individuals additional information on copyright and permissions richard l duchossois  wikipedia richard l duchossois from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search richard l duchossois born october   chicago illinois education morgan park academy washington and lee university occupation business executive with the duchossois group inc arlington park churchill downs board member of the duchossois group inc tcmc inc thoroughbred racing association spouses  beverly thrall  judi children craig j dayle bruce kim awards  bronze stars purple heart american jockey club gold medal special sovereign award  lord derby award palmer award for meritorious service to racing eclipse award of merit  chicagoland sports hall o