where she is active in mental health causes brother bruce is  and an amateur hunterjumper horseman another sister yearold kim heads the elmhurstbased duchossois foundation horse tale dick duchossois encountered joe joyce at a cocktail party in  and learned that madison square garden corp was considering putting its arlington park racetrack up for sale dick who already had a stable of horses at the track told joe hed bid for the track if joe who was president of arlington would stay on and run it for him joe agreed and dick was able to pick up arlington for less than  million a bargain price multitasking in the s dick duchossois worried the family was too narrowly invested in rail car manufacturing seeking to diversify he came across chamberlain manufacturing co headquartered in elmhurst a conglomerate of nine businesses the biggest made metal components for the defense industry the smallest made garage door openers the family acquired the company and over the years shed many of its pieces today just garage door openers and defense components remain there goes the neighborhood the barrington hills estate a compound of barns and stables called hill n dale farm is home to more than  horses neighbors in the rural environs fear it will be converted to a housing development after the elder duchossois is gone we have no plans to do anything with the farm but i dont intend to rule from the grave richard says h lee murphy  by crain communications inc arlington international racecourse inc todays crains get our daily roundup of important business news duchossois family to diversify investments  finance news  crains chicago business friday july   login register subscribe welcome guest account settings register log out navigation editors’ picks weather search heres how four loko became a thing again dorms for grownups come to chicago whos telling the truth about state school funding—rauner or dems when small manufacturers become the bank the doctor will see you now—for  × how c